oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex
Class BucketSeries

java.lang.Object
  oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex.BucketSeries
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class BucketSeries
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable

BucketSeries represents a series (collection) of buckets that are produced based on a particular classification scheme. It is mainly used by Advanced Styles such as BucketStyle and ColorSchemeStyle for thematic mapping. Given a Field object, MapViewer can quickly determine which Bucket in this BucketSeries contains the value of the Field. It can then get the associated rendering/labeling style from that Bucket, and apply them to any geogarphic feature with the given value. If none of the Buckets in this BucketSeries contains the Field's value, the default rendering/labeling styles serve as a backup option for rendering/labeling the features.

Parameters:

Returns:
int - the position index inside this BucketSeries (starting at 0) for the Bucket that contains the value; or -1 if no Bucket can be found for the Field value and there is no default Bucket.

setupEqualRangedBuckets

public void setupEqualRangedBuckets(double min,
                                    double max,
                                    int nBuckets)
Sets up equal ranged Buckets with given maximum and minum values for this BucketSeries. Any existing Buckets will be removed first. Each Bucket created will be automatically assigned an Id string unique within this BucketSeries. The bucket series schema will be SCHEME_EQUAL_INTERVAL. Note: the min is inclusive, while the max value is exclusive.

Parameters:
min - - the minimum value for this BucketSeries; value itself is included
max - - the maximum value for this BucketSeries; value itself is excluded
nBuckets - - the number of buckets
